result.reason: This is a known Windows OS-level limitation in mstscax.dll (MSTSC ActiveX COM control) which caps concurrent AxMsRdpClient* instances to ~14 per process; fixing it would require major architectural changes such as process isolation or switching to an alternative RDP backend (e.g. FreeRDP).
result.approach: Document as a known mstscax.dll per-process COM instance limit; users needing >14 simultaneous RDP sessions would need process isolation or an alternative RDP library — out of scope for current architecture
